32.5:
They corrupted themselves against him —
not his children, these, their moral stain disqualifies them;
a generation twisted and bent.

32.41:
'I will sharpen my flashing sword;
my hand will seize the instrument of judgment;
I will repay my enemies in full
and reward those who hate me.'

33.2:
The LORD came from Sinai;
he rose like the dawn from Seir;
he blazed forth from Mount Paran.
He came with ten thousands of his holy ones —
fire streaming from his right hand.

33.9:
'He said to father and mother, "I do not know you";
he would not acknowledge his brothers
or favor his own children.
He chose your word over every human bond;
he kept your covenant without flinching.'

33.20:
'Blessed be the one who expands Gad's territory!
Gad crouches like a lion;
he tears arm and scalp apart.'

33.25:
'Your fastening is iron and bronze;
and whatever the days bring,
your strength shall match them.'
